Nikos
 Anastasopoulos, heard of a workers' union for an Athens municipality, 
said: 'We just can't take it any more. There is desperation, anger and 
bitterness.'

Demonstrations during a similar 48-hour strike in June left the centre of Athens badly damaged as rioters clashed with police.

Piles
 of rubbish continue to rot on street corners despite a civil 
mobilisation order issued yesterday to order crews back to work after a 
